text:
Thanks for the PR @scfarley. Catching index error for malformed auth header is a great start. I think we can easily improve the resilience even more by returning an empty list if the Authorization header does not start with 'OAuth'. 

```
if authorization_header.startswith(auth_scheme):
    authorization_header = authorization_header.replace(auth_scheme, '', 1)
    items = parse_http_list(authorization_header)
    try:
        return list(parse_keqv_list(items).items())
    except (IndexError, ValueError):
        raise ValueError('Malformed authorization header')
else:
    return []
```
